A4.text: Liszt's main contribution to program music was his thirteen symphonic poems, one-movement orchestral works in which some extramusical program or idea provides a narrative or illustrative element.

A5.text: He is best known for his piano music, which forms the majority of his oeuvre, but he also wrote for orchestra and for other ensembles.
